		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Why not at the end of the *.NES file, add some bytes where the board name could be placed? Wouldn't that solve the issue with iNES? Older emulators wouldn't read the extra data, and newer ones could check for its existance and act on it if needed. I think that's a simple and effective solution, and would be very easy to use by homebrew developers and hackers. Just add something like 32 bytes at the end to put a standardized board name.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
