		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Hmm, nice to see someone (Bootgod, Martin) step up. The way I see it, this new format is meant for preservation only (iNES2 can still exist for everything else: gaming, development, romhacking). The emulator, Nestopia in this case, is used as a tool to see if the data/info extracted from the board is accurate.
<br />
<br />"preservationists" should be aware though that this is not the ultimate format, it's done in steps. 10 years ago we thought iNES was enough, 20 years from now, the information we have currently will probably be seen as lacking.

		

